  "prompt": "Is Ravana's golden lanka still in Sri Lanka?",
  "response": "Ravana's golden Lanka, as described in ancient Indian texts like the Ramayana, is a mythical kingdom associated with the demon king Ravana. The narrative presents Lanka as a magnificent and prosperous city made of gold. However, there is no archaeological evidence to support the existence of a literal \"golden Lanka\" as described in these texts.\n\nIn modern times, Sri Lanka is home to many historical and archaeological sites, and some locations are often associated with the tales from the Ramayana. While some places may be linked to Ravana's story, they are part of the cultural heritage and mythology rather than direct representations of an ancient golden city. Thus, Ravana's golden Lanka, in the literal sense, is not present in Sri Lanka today.",
